title: For Sale:  BAD BOYS QUAD .357 MAGNUM MOVIE GUN. (( COP .357 )) NEW IN BOX
postcontent:
THIS IS THE GUN FROM BAD BOYS 2 THE MOVIE...... (( not actual one used in the film ))

BRAND NEW IN THE BOX WITH ALL PAPER WORK.....

The COP 357 is a 4 shot Derringer type pistol chambered for the powerful .357 Magnum round. It is made of solid stainless steel components. Cartridges are loaded into the four separate chambers by sliding a latch that "pops-up" the barrel for loading purposes, similar to top-break shotguns. Each of the four chambers has its own dedicated firing pin. It uses an internal hammer, which is activated by depressing the trigger to hit a ratcheting/rotating striker that in turn strikes one firing pin at a time. Older "pepperboxes" also used multiple barrels, but the barrels were the part that rotated. The COP 357 operates similarly to the Sharps rimfire pepperbox of the 1850s, in that it uses the ratcheting/rotating striker, which is completely internal, to fire each chamber in sequence.

This high velocity 45 acp+P load offers numerous tactical advantages for anyone using their 45 acp pistol for anti-personnel purposes. First, this load is operating at velocities of normal +P 9MM 115gr. ammo, yet it is a 45 caliber, 160gr. bullet. Second, this load will penetrate roughly 15 to 18 inches of penetration in flesh and bone, depending on which bones are hit. Third, this load generates relatively low recoil because of the light weight bullet, which assists in fast follow-up shots. Fourth, we are as per usual, using a low flash powder, so the shooter is not blinded by his own gunfire should he be required to drop the hammer in low light, when the criminal element is most active.

This 45 ACP +P load is safe for use in ALL 45 ACP pistols that are in normal operating condition.

postcontent:
!!! If this ad is still active the gun is for sale.  I will not respond to "is this gun still available" emails !!!

This is a copy of the famous (and expensive) Browning SA.22 takedown semi auto rifle.  It is made by Interarms and is very well made, very reliable, and very accurate.  It breaks down in seconds without any tools and reassembles just as easily.  Broken down each piece is roughly 18” so it’s a perfect backpack or camping rifle that’s fully capable of getting the job done.  It only shoots 22lr (not 22 shorts or 22 magnums).

This rifle is NIB (New In Box) and is therefore in absolutely perfect condition.  I have 2 of these and decided to let one go.

These rifles have nice checkering on the stock and forearm with a high gloss finish and the bluing is quite nice too.  There is some light scroll work on each side of the receiver (sorry my picture is a bit blurry).

You load this gun through a loading tube in the stock (hold 11) and it ejects the empties out the bottom of the receiver. These were only imported by Interarms for a short period in the 80’s.

Not looking for trades.  FTF in Greensboro.  All laws will be followed and you'll need to sign a bill of sale.
